Interface StreamingVideo


  • public interface StreamingVideo
    This abstract data type represents the backend for a streaming video service. It stores the videos (TV episodes and films), TV series, and users in the system, as well as the ratings that users assign to videos.

    • Method Detail

      • addVideo

        boolean addVideo(Video newVideo)
          throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                 SetFullException

        Adds a new video to the collection if newVideo is not null, there is room in the collection, and if newVideo does not already exist in the collection without altering any other videos. Method will return true if the add operation is successful, otherwise it will throw setFullException if the collection is full. If newVideo is null, addVideo will throw a nullPointerException without changing the collection. If the newVideo is already in the collection it will return false.

        Parameters:
        newVideo - the video to be added to collection
        Returns:
        true if the add operation is successfull, false if the video already exists in the collection
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if newVideo is null
        SetFullException - if the collection is full and cannot add a video

If videoElem is null, remmoveVideo throws nullPointerException

        Returns:

        Throws:

      • addToSeries

        boolean addToSeries(TvEpisode newTvEpisode,
                    TvSeries tvSeriesElem)
             throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                    SetFullException
        Adds an existing television episode to an existing television series if newTvEpisode and the TV series is not null, there is room in the collection, and if newTvEpisode does not already exist in the collection without altering any other videos. Method will return true if the add operation is successful, otherwise it will throw a setFullException if the collection is full. If newTvEpisode or if the TV series is null, addToSeries will throw a nullPointerException without changing the collection. If the newTvEpisode is already in the collection it will return false
        Parameters:
        newTvEpisode - the TvEpisode to be added to collection
        tvSeriesElem - the TV series to which the newTvEpisode will be added
        Returns:
        true if the add operation is successfull, false if the TvEpisode already exists in the collection or in the TvSeries
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if newTvEpisode or if tvSeriesElem is null
        SetFullException - if the collection is full and cannot add a TvEpisode

      • removeFromSeries

        void removeFromSeries(TvEpisode tvEpisodeElem,
                      TvSeries tvSeriesElem)
               throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Removes a television episode from an exisiting television series if both the TvSeries and TvEpisode are not null without changing other elements in the collection. Method will throw NullPointerException if either paramater is null. If the TvSeries is not in the system, method will throw an IllegalArgumentException. If the TvEpisode is not in the given TvSeries, method throws IllegalArgumentException.
        Parameters:
        tvEpisodeElem - the TvEpisode to be removed from the collection
        tvSeriesElem - the TV series to which the TvEpisode will be removed
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the tvEpisodeElem or tvSeriesElem is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if tvEpisodeElem or tvSeriesElem is not in the collection

      • rateVideo

        void rateVideo(User userElem,
               Video videoElem,
               int rating)
        throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
               java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Sets a user's rating for a video, as a number of stars from 1 to 5 if no rating already exists. If a rating does exists for the video and is different than the origianl rating, the old rating is replaced with the new rating. If either the User or the Video is null, method throws NullPointerException.
        Parameters:
        userElem - an exisiting user that rates a video
        videoElem - the video given a rating
        rating - the int value representing the star rating from 1 to 5
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the rating is outside the range of 1 to 5 and if either the user or video is not in the collection
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the user or the video is null

      • clearRating

        void clearRating(User theUser,
                 Video theVideo)
          throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                 java.lang.NullPointerException,
                 java.util.NoSuchElementException
        Clears a user's rating on a video. If this user has rated this video and the rating has not already been cleared, then the rating is cleared and the state will appear as if the rating was never made. If there is no such rating on record (either because this user has not rated this video, or because the rating has already been cleared), then this method will throw an IllegalArgumentException. If the user or video is not in the system, then this method will throw NoSuchElementException.
        Parameters:
        theUser - user whose rating should be cleared
        theVideo - video from which the user's rating should be cleared
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the user does not currently have a rating on record for the video
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - if either the user or the video is not in the system
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if either the user or the video is null

      • predictRating

        double predictRating(User userElem,
                     Video videoElem)
              throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                     java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Predicts the rating a user will assign to a video that they have not yet rated, as a number of stars from 1 to 5 as a double number. If the video already has a rating the method throws an IllegalArgumentException. If the User or Video is null, the method will throw a NullPointerException. If neither the user or the video is in the collection, method will throw an IllegalArgumentException. The method will predict the rating of a valid video based in the users previous rated videos. If no videos are rated by the user, the method returns null.
        Parameters:
        userElem - the user for which the predicted rate will be made
        videoElem - the video to which the method will predict the rating
        Returns:
        the predicted rating of the video as a double
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if either the user or video are null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the user or video are not in the collection or if the video already has a rating

      • suggestVideo

        Video suggestVideo(User userElem)
            throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                   java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns a video for a user that they are predicted to like if the video and user is valid. If the user is null, method throws a NullPointerException. If the user is not in the collection, method throws an IllegalArgumentException.
        Parameters:
        userElem - the user for which the video is sugegested
        Returns:
        the suggested video
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the user is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the user is not in the collection or if the suggested video is not in the collection
